OL,3,CNSPCC calls for 'law change' to
OL,4,Cprotect children from all physical
OL,5,Cpunishment
OL,7,FIt argues this would give clarity in
OL,8,Fthe law, and children in Northern
OL,9,FIreland the same protection from
OL,10,Fassault as their counterparts in other
OL,11,Fparts of the UK and Ireland.
OL,13,FNSPCC said their research from 2022
OL,14,Frevealed that in Northern Ireland,
OL,15,Falmost two thirds (65%) of adults
OL,16,Fsupported a change in the law to
OL,17,Fprotect children from being physically
OL,18,Fpunished by their parents and carers.
OL,20,FAmong parents, carers and guardians
OL,21,Fthe support rose to 71%.
