OL,5,Cpunishment
OL,7,F"Where available evidence exists, it
OL,8,Fsuggests that in jurisdictions where
OL,9,Fequal protection has been implemented,
OL,10,Fthe most common intervention in
OL,11,Fresponse to referrals has been
OL,12,Fparenting support, crucially this
OL,13,Fprovides a juncture to identify
OL,14,Fpotential abuse or support families to
OL,15,Fhelp children thrive.
OL,17,F"A legal change is necessary to
OL,18,Fprovide clarity and encourage the best
OL,19,Foutcomes for children.
